                            <comment id="12730297" author="adeneche" created="Mon, 13 Jul 2009 12:32:53 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;I have two questions:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;This is related to &lt;a href=&quot;http://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HADOOP-1230&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;HADOOP-1230 &lt;/a&gt; right ? does it mean that when using &lt;b&gt;org.apache.hadoop.mapreduce&lt;/b&gt; instead of &lt;b&gt;org.apache.hadoop.mapred&lt;/b&gt;, mahout won&apos;t work on hadoop 0.19.1 anymore ?&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;In case that mahout won&apos;t work on hadoop 0.19.1, does anyone know a 0.20.0 AMI to use with Amazon EC2 ?&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="12731654" author="gsingers" created="Wed, 15 Jul 2009 21:09:54 +0100"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;This is related to &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HADOOP-1230&quot; title=&quot;Replace parameters with context objects in Mapper, Reducer, Partitioner, InputFormat, and OutputFormat classes&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HADOOP-1230&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HADOOP-1230&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;  right ? does it mean that when using org.apache.hadoop.mapreduce instead of org.apache.hadoop.mapred, mahout won&apos;t work on hadoop 0.19.1 anymore ?&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Not sure if it will work, we didn&apos;t actually change over anything just yet.  See &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MAHOUT-143&quot; title=&quot;Refactor Hadoop deprecations&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;MAHOUT-143&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;MAHOUT-143&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;In case that mahout won&apos;t work on hadoop 0.19.1, does anyone know a 0.20.0 AMI to use with Amazon EC2 ?&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Not sure.  It&apos;s not too hard to make one, right?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12784093" author="srowen" created="Tue, 1 Dec 2009 07:15:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m going to hijack this issue, to track my progress to get the new-style Hadoop APIs working. As far as I can tell there are at least a few critical problems with the new APIs in 0.20.x, that appear to be resolved in 0.21.x. I am currently trying to get everything working in org.apache.cf.taste.hadoop with 0.21.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12784213" author="srowen" created="Tue, 1 Dec 2009 12:54:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Here are the facts I&apos;ve gathered after a lot of experimentation:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;0.22 is way too bleeding edge &amp;#8211; our code doesn&apos;t even compile against it.&lt;br/&gt;
0.21 compiles, but the docs and tools aren&apos;t quite in place. With some hacking, I got the cluster partly up but not completely, and am already far enough in to feel this is also too bleeding edge.&lt;br/&gt;
0.20 runs our code that&apos;s written for old 0.19 APIs. It runs some of the code written for 0.20 APIs but not all &amp;#8211; has bugs only fixed in 0.21&lt;br/&gt;
0.19 works of course, but isn&apos;t the latest release and its APIs are deprecated&lt;br/&gt;
0.18 is what stuff like Amazon Elastic Mapreduce runs&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So, I can&apos;t make progress on 0.20. I can make progress on 0.21 I imagine, but when it comes out. &lt;br/&gt;
I can move back to use 0.19 APIs (which hopefully work on 0.18 too). It will work on 0.20. That would at least put us on one consistent version of Hadoop, and back in a working state.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I suggest we do not move to new APIs en masse until 0.21 is released and stabilizes.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12871894" author="srowen" created="Wed, 26 May 2010 20:03:39 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Resolving this after my last change, since I think what&apos;s left is covered in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MAHOUT-167&quot; title=&quot;Convert code to Hadoop 0.20 API&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;MAHOUT-167&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;MAHOUT-167&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
